Contract CO1: createTask
Operation:
creatTask(String title, String description, Priority priority,
Date completeBy)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The task title is provided and correct.
  - The priority is chosen.

Postcodition:
  - A new Task object is created (object creation)
  - Task attributes including title, description, priority, the completion date, the
  date it was created, and status) are all set using the (attribute modification)
  - A new ActivityEntry object is created (object creation)
  - The ActivityEntry then gets associated with the Task (association formed)
  - The ActivityEntry's attributes such as timestamp and description are set (attribute modification)

Contract C02: removeTask
Operation:
removeTask(int taskId)

Preconditions:
  - The system is running and online.
  - The task that needs to be removed exists

Posconditions:
- The status of the task is changed to cancelled (attribute modification)
- The task remains still in the system and does not get deleted
- A new ActivityEntry pbject is created (object creation)
- The ActivityEntry object is associated with the Task (association formed)
- The ActivityEntry's attributes such as timestamp and description are set (attribute modification)

